<div class="xar-mod-head"><span class="xar-mod-title"><xar:mlstring>Multisites Administration</xar:mlstring></span></div>
<div class="xar-mod-body">
    <h2><xar:mlstring>Overview</xar:mlstring></h2>
    <div style="padding: 1px;" class="xar-norm-outline">
        <div style="float:right;padding:10px;">
            <xar:if condition="file_exists('modules/multisites/xarimages/admin.gif')" >
               <img src="modules/multisites/xarimages/admin.gif" alt="official icon" width="96" height="96" />
            <xar:else /> <img src="modules/multisites/xarimages/admin_generic.gif" alt="official icon" width="96" height="96" />
            </xar:if>
         </div>
        <div class="xar-mod-title xar-norm-outline" style="margin-top: 1em; margin-left: 1em; margin-right: 1em; width: auto; border-style: none none dotted none;">
            <xar:mlstring>What is it?</xar:mlstring>
        </div>
        <div style="margin-left: 1em; margin-right: 1em; text-align:left;">
            
      <p><xar:mlstring>The Multisites Module automates the creation of Xaraya 
        multisites and eventually their configuration. Using Xaraya Multisites, 
        a Site Administrator can create and run multiple Xaraya sites from a single 
        master installation of Xaraya.</xar:mlstring></p>
            
      <p><xar:mlstring>At this time, the Multisites Module is not complete but
        it will setup basic scripts required to run your multisites.</xar:mlstring></p>
        </div>
        <div class="xar-mod-title xar-norm-outline" style="margin-top: 1em; margin-left: 1em; margin-right: 1em; width: auto; border-style: none none dotted none;">
            <xar:mlstring>How to use it?</xar:mlstring>
        </div>
        <div style="margin-left: 1em; margin-right: 1em; text-align:left;">
            
      <p><xar:mlstring>To use Xaraya multisites, you must have all domain and 
        subdomains that you wish to use for your 'subsites' resolving to the same 
        IP as your master Xaraya site domain name, or pointed to the same directory 
        as your main Xaraya install. </xar:mlstring></p>
      <p><xar:mlstring>Assuming you already have your main site installed, run 
        the Xaraya Installer to install the database tables for your new subsite. Make
        sure you protect the master config.system.php file found in the /var directory
        so that it is not overwritten by the install process. Copy it out, and then put it back when 
        you have finished the install for the subsite.</xar:mlstring></p>
      <p><xar:mlstring>From the menu, you have four choices:</xar:mlstring></p>
        </div>
        
    <ul>
      <li> <xar:mlstring>Add Site - Once you have set up the Master Multisite 
        Configuration</xar:mlstring>, you can use this option to set up a subsite. 
        At this time, the option only creates the required directory tree and 
        config.system.php file for your subsite. <br>
      </li>
      <li> <xar:mlstring>View Sites - This option lists the Master site and all 
        subsites. At this time, that is all it does :-)<br>
        </xar:mlstring></li>
      <li> <xar:mlstring>Admin Config - The admin configuration just sets the 
        number of sites listed per page in the View Sites option.<br>
        </xar:mlstring></li>
      <li>Master Config - Choose this option first to set up the basic configuration 
        requirements to run your multisites. This option changes your master config.system.php 
        file so it can recognize your subsites, and also creates the main subsite 
        data directory and directory tree used for individual subsite configuration.</li>
    </ul>
        <div class="xar-mod-title xar-norm-outline" style="margin-top: 1em; margin-left: 1em; margin-right: 1em; width: auto; border-style: none none dotted none;">
          <xar:mlstring>Included Blocks</xar:mlstring>
        </div>
        <br />
        <div style="margin-left: 1em; margin-right: 1em; text-align:left;">
            <xar:mlstring>Multisites Module has no blocks included at this time.</xar:mlstring>
        </div>
         <br />
        <div class="xar-mod-title xar-norm-outline" style="margin-top: 1em; margin-left: 1em; margin-right: 1em; width: auto; border-style: none none dotted none;">
           <xar:mlstring>Included Hooks</xar:mlstring>
        </div>
        <br />
        <div style="margin-left: 1em; margin-right: 1em; text-align:left;">
           <xar:mlstring>The Multisites Module has no hooks included.</xar:mlstring>
        </div>
        <br />
        <div class="xar-norm-outline xar-accent" style="text-align: center; padding: 0.5em 1em 0.5em 1em; margin-top: 5px;">
           <xar:mlstring>Extended information about this module can be found here. [modules module]</xar:mlstring>
        </div>
      </div>
  </div>
<div align="center">
<b><xar:var scope="session" name="$multisites_statusmsg" /></b>
</div>
